====Usage notes====
Following French, {{term|blond||lang=en}} is often used to describe males while {{term||blonde|lang=en}} is often used to describe females. However, in English, the distinction is not always made. Particularly in the US, {{term|blond}} has been used as a gender-neutral term since the 1970s.

